travel document issued by United Kingdom. \nMy question is do I need to get evisa  to visit Moldova for purpose of tourism? \nBecause I was trying to apply evisa but its came up as YOU ARE EXEMPTED FROM THE OBLIGATION TO HOLD THIS TYPE OF VISA.\nPlease advise me I\'m eligible to get on arrival visa .\nI have attached the copy of my travel document. ','We would like to bring to your attention that according to the GOVERNMENT DECISION No. 765 dated 18-09-2014 on the approval of the list of travel documents accepted for crossing the state border of the Republic of Moldova by foreigners the travel document for refugees (Convention relating to the Status of Refugees of 28 July 1951) or the travel document for Stateless Persons (Convention Relating to the Status of Stateless Persons of 28 September 1954)  issued by the authorities of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland is accepted by the Republic of Moldova for crossing the border.\nWe also inform you that according to the Law No. 257 of 01-11-2013 on third-country nationals who are required to hold a visa and third-country nationals who are exempted from the visa requirement when crossing the state border of the Republic of Moldova, nationals of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland do not need a visa for entry/exit/transit of the Republic of Moldova.\nAdditionally, Article 6 of Law No. 200 dated July 16, 2010, on the regime of foreigners in the Republic of Moldova, applies to you upon entry into the country, specifically:\nArticle 6.1 Requirements for Travel Documents\n1.	At the time of entry into the territory of the Republic of Moldova, the validity of the travel document must exceed the intended date of departure from the territory of the Republic of Moldova by at least three months.\n2.	In exceptional cases, as provided by paragraph (1) of Article 21, and in the case of international officials participating in important events of national or international significance organized by the central public authorities, entry into the Republic of Moldova is permitted based on a travel document with a validity period of less than three months after the intended date of departure.\n3.	The travel document must contain at least two blank pages.\n4.	The travel document must have been issued within the last 10 years.\n5.	The provisions of paragraphs (3) and (4) do not apply to identification cards approved for crossing the state border.\nAccording to the law 28, dated 15-02-2024 regarding the state border of the Republic of Moldova ,\nArticle 25. Specific Conditions for the Control of Foreign Nationals\n(1) In accordance with Article 23, border police officers have the right to request justification for the purpose of entry into the Republic of Moldova. Foreign nationals are required to provide information and documents confirming the purpose of their entry:\n1.	For business travel:\na) An invitation from a company, organization, or institution;\nb) Documents confirming an economic interest (e.g., power of attorney, employment contract, tickets, or invitations to exhibitions).\n2.	For study or other types of training:\na) A document certifying enrollment in an educational institution or another form of training;\nb) A student ID or a certificate confirming attendance in a course.\n3.	For tourism or personal reasons:\na) Proof of accommodation at a hotel or an invitation from a host stating the guest\'s accommodation address;\nb) Confirmation of a reservation for an organized trip or any other relevant document indicating the planned travel itinerary;\nc) A return or round-trip ticket.\n4.	For travel undertaken for political, scientific, cultural, sports, religious events, or other purposes:\no	Invitations, entrance tickets, programs listing, where possible, the name of the host organization and the duration of the visit, or any other relevant document indicating the purpose of the visit','eng','2025-04-08 23:45:45.432502','2025-04-08 23:45:45.432502',