travel document must exceed the intended date of departure from the territory of the Republic of Moldova by at least three months.\n2.	In exceptional cases, as provided by paragraph (1) of Article 21, and in the case of international officials participating in important events of national or international significance organized by the central public authorities, entry into the Republic of Moldova is permitted based on a travel document with a validity period of less than three months after the intended date of departure.\n3.	The travel document must contain at least two blank pages.\n4.	The travel document must have been issued within the last 10 years.\n5.	The provisions of paragraphs (3) and (4) do not apply to identification cards approved for crossing the state border.\nAt the same time, we inform you that in accordance with Law 28 of 15-02-2024\nArticle 25. Specific conditions for control\nof foreigners\n(1) Under the conditions of art. 23, border guards have the right to request justification of the purpose of entry of foreigners into the Republic of Moldova, who are obliged to present information and documents confirming the purpose of entry:\n1) for business trips:\na) an invitation from an enterprise, organization or institution;\nb) documents confirming an economic interest (for example: power of attorney, employment contract, tickets or invitations to participate in exhibitions);\n2) for trips for the purpose of study or other types of training:\na) a document certifying enrollment in an educational institution or other forms of training;\nb) student card or certificate of course attendance;\n3) for tourist trips or personal reasons:\na) a document confirming hotel accommodation, an invitation from the host indicating the guest’s accommodation address;\nb) confirmation of a reservation for an organized trip or any other appropriate document indicating the travel plans to be undertaken;\nc) a return or onward ticket;\n4) for trips undertaken for political, scientific, cultural, sporting purposes, on the occasion of religious events or for other purposes: invitations, entrance tickets, programs indicating, where possible, the name of the host organization and the duration of the visit or any other appropriate document indicating the purpose of the visit;\n(2) During the validity period of the decision on non-authorization of entry to the territory of the Republic of Moldova, border control procedures may not be resumed for the purpose of authorizing the entry of the foreigner into the country.\nIn simple terms, your passport must be valid for at least 3 months from the date of your return ticket.\n\nWe also inform you that the decision regarding the authorization to cross the State Border is approved at the State Border crossing point at the time of crossing and belongs to the border police officer who checks the valid travel documents presented at the check and ensures that the foreigner meets all the conditions for crossing.','eng','2025-04-08 23:45:45.432502','2025-04-08 23:45:45.432502','[-0.316925585269928, 0.33000314235687256, -0.05798638239502907, -0.356089323759079, 0.1647808700799942, 0.025108693167567253, 0.14321275055408478, -0.14164282381534576, -0.19619464874267578, 0.12307768315076828, -0.004768682643771172, 0.2170318216085434, -0.1370382159948349, 0.09683091193437576, 0.21051207184791565, -0.2207104116678238, 0.13794273138046265, 0.25394442677497864, -0.072891004383564, -0.06477689743041992, -0.11088024824857712, 0.03137918934226036, -0.05467446893453598, 0.20114178955554962, 0.2754671275615692, 0.20131592452526093, -0.03906866908073425, -0.15651625394821167, -0.12771405279636383, 0.17600739002227783, 0.2341063916683197, 0.0018719970248639584, -0.10478420555591583, -0.10893909633159637, 0.15276747941970825, 0.056019511073827744, -0.05332166329026222, -0.19601477682590485, 0.14794482290744781, 0.15940582752227783, 0.07249191403388977, 0.3158029019832611, -0.146841898560524, 0.24646615982055664, 0.2473362